The Gumroad MCP server is an implementation of the Model Context Protocol that allows AI assistants, such as Claude Desktop, to interact with the Gumroad API [1][2][3]. It enables users to perform tasks like listing products, viewing sales data, managing subscription details, and handling offer codes directly through natural language prompts [2][4][5].

To configure the server manually for an MCP-compatible client, add this to your configuration file [1][5]:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "gumroad": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "gumroad-mcp@latest"],
      "env": {
        "GUMROAD_ACCESS_TOKEN": "<YOUR_TOKEN>"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

Installation for Claude Desktop can also be performed via the interactive command `npx gumroad-mcp@latest init` [5]. Prerequisities include Node.js 18 or later and a Gumroad access token [4][5].
